# ============================================================
# calendar.txt   -   one event per line: YYYY-MM-DD  description
# Tags (@birthday @health @car @family @subscription @bill @trial ...) are
# OPTIONAL; add one when an entry is worth flagging or filtering later.
#
# Tag style: calendar.txt uses @tag (todo.txt style). LIFE.TXT uses
# colon-delimited :tag: tokens, space-separated. The difference is
# intentional - each file follows its own lineage, and :tag: colons delimit
# tags within the free-form prose of LIFE.TXT, where @ alone could be
# ambiguous.
#
# View:  agenda     (today highlighted + upcoming; see: agenda --help)
# Edit:  vi <path>/calendar.txt   - type a dated line anywhere, save.
#
# Layout: entries are kept interleaved in DATE order, so reading the raw file
# (cat calendar.txt) shows your timeline - what is coming up, next by next.
# agenda sorts by date at read time regardless, so order is for YOUR reading.
#
#   Re-sort after edits:  in vi, put the cursor on the first dated line and run
#                         :.,$!sort      (sorts that line to end; leaves this
#                         header alone; leading YYYY-MM-DD sorts as plain text)
#   Grouped view by type: grep @birthday <path>/calendar.txt
#   Annual birthdays:     set the full date to the next occurrence; bump the
#                         year in place as each passes, then re-sort as above.
#
# NOTE: This is a template. The example dates below are illustrative -
# replace them with your own. (Being in the past, they will not show as
# upcoming in agenda until you edit them.)
#
# NOTE: Location is adjustable. agenda reads it from $LIFE_DIR (default ~/life,
# so ~/life/calendar.txt). Set LIFE_DIR to point elsewhere, e.g.
# /mnt/usbflashdrive/life/calendar.txt on a machine using a USB drive.
# ============================================================

2026-06-26  @subscription  ExampleWeekly - weekly (re-seed as it passes)
2026-06-30  @trial  Example Service trial ends 2026-07-01 - cancel or keep?
2026-07-02  @health  Dr. - annual checkup 9:30am
2026-07-03  @subscription  ExampleWeekly - weekly
2026-07-12  @subscription  Netflix - monthly. Still want it?
2026-07-12  @subscription  TSN - monthly. Still want it?
2026-07-15  @bill  Mortgage payment due (15th monthly)
2026-09-05  @birthday @family  John Vega (b. 1980)
2027-03-12  @birthday @family  Jane Doe (b. 1973)
